  <Name>k__BackingField: Proverbs
  fancyName: 
  nickname: pro
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Beginning of Knowledge'
      title: The Beginning of Knowledge
      number: 1
      content: '    The proverbs of Solomon, son of David, king of Israel:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'To know wisdom and instruction,to understand words of insight,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'to receive instruction in wise dealing,in righteousness, justice,
        and equity;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "to give prudence to the simple,knowledge and discretion to the youth\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Let the wise hear and increase in learning,and the one who understands
        obtain guidance,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'to understand a proverb and a saying,  the words of the wise and
        their riddles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Enticement of Sinners'
      title: The Enticement of Sinners
      number: 7
      content: '  The fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is the beginning of
        knowledge;fools despise wisdom and instruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  Hear, my son, your father\u2019s instruction,and forsake not your
        mother\u2019s teaching,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'for they are a graceful garland for your headand pendants for your
        neck.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'My son, if sinners entice you,do not consent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "If they say, \u201CCome with us, let us lie in wait for blood;  let
        us ambush the innocent without reason;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'like Sheol let us swallow them alive,and whole, like those who go
        down to the pit;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'we shall find all precious goods,we shall fill our houses with plunder;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "throw in your lot among us;we will all have one purse\u201D\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'my son, do not walk in the way with them;  hold back your foot from
        their paths,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'for their feet run to evil,and they make haste to shed blood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  For in vain is a net spreadin the sight of any bird,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'but these men lie in wait for their own blood;they set an ambush
        for their own lives.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Call of Wisdom'
      title: The Call of Wisdom
      number: 19
      content: '  Such are the ways of everyone who is greedy for unjust gain;  it
        takes away the life of its possessors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Wisdom cries aloud in the street,in the markets she raises her
        voice;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'at the head of the noisy streets she cries out;at the entrance of
        the city gates she speaks:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CHow long, O simple ones, will you love being simple?How long
        will scoffers delight in their scoffingand fools hate knowledge?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'If you turn at my reproof,[[COMMENT(0)]]behold, I will pour out my
        spirit to you;I will make my words known to you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:23 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  Because I have called and you refused to listen,have stretched
        out my hand and no one has heeded,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'because you have ignored all my counseland would have none of my
        reproof,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'I also will laugh at your calamity;I will mock when terror strikes
        you,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'when terror strikes you like a stormand your calamity comes like
        a whirlwind,when distress and anguish come upon you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  Then they will call upon me, but I will not answer;they will seek
        me diligently but will not find me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Because they hated knowledgeand did not choose the fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  would have none of my counseland despised all my reproof,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'therefore they shall eat the fruit of their way,and have their fill
        of their own devices.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For the simple are killed by their turning away,and the complacency
        of fools destroys them;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "but whoever listens to me will dwell secureand will be at ease, without
        dread of disaster.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Value of Wisdom'
      title: The Value of Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: '    My son, if you receive my wordsand treasure up my commandments
        with you,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'making your ear attentive to wisdomand inclining your heart to understanding;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'yes, if you call out for insightand raise your voice for understanding,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'if you seek it like silverand search for it as for hidden treasures,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'then you will understand the fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>and
        find the knowledge of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gives wisdom;from his mouth come
        knowledge and understanding;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'he stores up sound wisdom for the upright;he is a shield to those
        who walk in integrity,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'guarding the paths of justiceand watching over the way of his saints.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Then you will understand righteousness and justiceand equity, every
        good path;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'for wisdom will come into your heart,and knowledge will be pleasant
        to your soul;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  discretion will watch over you,understanding will guard you,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'delivering you from the way of evil,from men of perverted speech,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'who forsake the paths of uprightnessto walk in the ways of darkness,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'who rejoice in doing eviland delight in the perverseness of evil,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'men whose paths are crooked,  and who are devious in their ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So you will be delivered from the forbidden[[COMMENT(0)]] woman,from
        the adulteress with her smooth words,  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew Hebrew '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'who forsakes the companion of her youthand forgets the covenant of
        her God;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  for her house sinks down to death,and her paths to the departed;[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'none who go to her come back,nor do they regain the paths of life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So you will walk in the way of the goodand keep to the paths of the
        righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For the upright will inhabit the land,and those with integrity will
        remain in it,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: but the wicked will be cut off from the land,and the treacherous will
        be rooted out of it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Trust in the  with All Your Heart'
      title: Trust in the  with All Your Heart
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    My son, do not forget my teaching, 
        but let your heart keep my commandments,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'for length of days and years of lifeand peace they will add to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Let not steadfast love and faithfulness forsake you;  bind them around
        your neck;  write them on the tablet of your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So you will find favor and good success[[COMMENT(0)]]in the sight
        of God and man.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Trust in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with all your heart,and
        do not lean on your own understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In all your ways acknowledge him,and he will make straight your paths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Be not wise in your own eyes;  fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and turn away from evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'It will be healing to your flesh[[COMMENT(0)]]and refreshment to
        your bones.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Honor the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> with your wealthand with the
        firstfruits of all your produce;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'then your barns will be filled with plenty,and your vats will be
        bursting with wine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  My son, do not despise the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s disciplineor
        be weary of his reproof,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Blessed Is the One Who Finds Wisdom'
      title: Blessed Is the One Who Finds Wisdom
      number: 12
      content: 'for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> reproves him whom he loves,as
        a father the son in whom he delights.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Blessed is the one who finds wisdom,and the one who gets understanding,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  for the gain from her is better than gain from silverand her profit
        better than gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'She is more precious than jewels,and nothing you desire can compare
        with her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  Long life is in her right hand;in her left hand are riches and
        honor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Her ways are ways of pleasantness,and all her paths are peace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'She is a tree of life to those who lay hold of her;those who hold
        her fast are called blessed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> by wisdom founded the earth;by
        understanding he established the heavens;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'by his knowledge the deeps broke open,and the clouds drop down the
        dew.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "My son, do not lose sight of these\u2014keep sound wisdom and discretion,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and they will be life for your souland adornment for your neck.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Then you will walk on your way securely,  and your foot will not
        stumble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  If you lie down, you will not be afraid;when you lie down, your
        sleep will be sweet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  Do not be afraid of sudden terroror of the ruin[[COMMENT(0)]] of
        the wicked, when it comes,  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:25 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be your confidenceand will
        keep your foot from being caught.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  Do not withhold good from those to whom it is due,[[COMMENT(0)]]when
        it is in your power to do it.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:27 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  Do not say to your neighbor, \u201CGo, and come again,tomorrow
        I will give it\u201D\u2014when you have it with you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  Do not plan evil against your neighbor,who dwells trustingly beside
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  Do not contend with a man for no reason,when he has done you no
        harm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  Do not envy a man of violenceand do not choose any of his ways,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'for the devious person is an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,but
        the upright are in his confidence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s curse is on the house of
        the wicked,but he blesses the dwelling of the righteous.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Toward the scorners he is scornful,  but to the humble he gives favor.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:34 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: The wise will inherit honor,but fools get[[COMMENT(0)]] disgrace.
      comments:
      - number: '3:35 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain
  - verses:
    - name: "1: A Father\u2019s Wise Instruction"
      title: "A Father\u2019s Wise Instruction"
      number: 1
      content: "    Hear, O sons, a father\u2019s instruction,and be attentive, that
        you may gain[[COMMENT(0)]] insight,  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'for I give you good precepts;do not forsake my teaching.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When I was a son with my father,  tender, the only one in the sight
        of my mother,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "he taught me and said to me,  \u201CLet your heart hold fast my words; 
        keep my commandments, and live.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Get wisdom; get insight;do not forget, and do not turn away from
        the words of my mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Do not forsake her, and she will keep you;  love her, and she will
        guard you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The beginning of wisdom is this: Get wisdom,and whatever you get,
        get insight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Prize her highly, and she will exalt you;she will honor you if you
        embrace her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "She will place on your head a graceful garland;she will bestow on
        you a beautiful crown.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Hear, my son, and accept my words,that the years of your life may
        be many.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I have taught you the way of wisdom;I have led you in the paths of
        uprightness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When you walk, your step will not be hampered,and if you run, you
        will not stumble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Keep hold of instruction; do not let go;guard her, for she is your
        life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Do not enter the path of the wicked,and do not walk in the way
        of the evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Avoid it; do not go on it;turn away from it and pass on.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For they cannot sleep unless they have done wrong;they are robbed
        of sleep unless they have made someone stumble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For they eat the bread of wickedness  and drink the wine of violence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But the path of the righteous is like the light of dawn,which shines
        brighter and brighter until full day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  The way of the wicked is like deep darkness;they do not know over
        what they stumble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  My son, be attentive to my words;incline your ear to my sayings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Let them not escape from your sight;  keep them within your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For they are life to those who find them,and healing to all their[[COMMENT(0)]]
        flesh.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:22 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Keep your heart with all vigilance,for from it flow the springs of
        life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Put away from you crooked speech,and put devious talk far from you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  Let your eyes look directly forward,and your gaze be straight before
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  Ponder[[COMMENT(0)]] the path of your feet;  then all your ways
        will be sure.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:26 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  Do not swerve to the right or to the left;turn your foot away from
        evil.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warning Against Adultery'
      title: Warning Against Adultery
      number: 1
      content: '    My son, be attentive to my wisdom;  incline your ear to my understanding,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that you may keep discretion,and your lips may guard knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For the lips of a forbidden[[COMMENT(0)]] woman drip honey,and her
        speech is smoother than oil,  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:3 '
        content: 'Hebrew ; also verse 20Hebrew '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'but in the end she is bitter as wormwood,  sharp as a two-edged sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Her feet go down to death;her steps follow the path to[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Sheol;  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'she does not ponder the path of life;her ways wander, and she does
        not know it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And now, O sons, listen to me,and do not depart from the words of
        my mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Keep your way far from her,and do not go near the door of her house,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'lest you give your honor to othersand your years to the merciless,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'lest strangers take their fill of your strength,and your labors go
        to the house of a foreigner,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and at the end of your life you groan,when your flesh and body are
        consumed,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "and you say, \u201CHow I hated discipline,and my heart despised reproof!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I did not listen to the voice of my teachersor incline my ear to
        my instructors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  I am at the brink of utter ruinin the assembled congregation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Drink water from your own cistern,flowing water from your own well.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Should your springs be scattered abroad,streams of water in the streets?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Let them be for yourself alone,and not for strangers with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Let your fountain be blessed,and rejoice in the wife of your youth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'a lovely deer, a graceful doe.Let her breasts fill you at all times
        with delight;be intoxicated[[COMMENT(0)]] always in her love.  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:19 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verse 20
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Why should you be intoxicated, my son, with a forbidden womanand
        embrace the bosom of an adulteress?[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:20 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "For a man\u2019s ways are before the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        he ponders[[COMMENT(0)]] all his paths.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:21 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The iniquities of the wicked ensnare him,and he is held fast in the
        cords of his sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  He dies for lack of discipline,and because of his great folly he
        is led astray.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Practical Warnings'
      title: Practical Warnings
      number: 1
      content: '  My son, if you have put up security for your neighbor,have given
        your pledge for a stranger,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'if you are snared in the words of your mouth,caught in the words
        of your mouth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'then do this, my son, and save yourself,for you have come into the
        hand of your neighbor:go, hasten,[[COMMENT(0)]] and plead urgently with your
        neighbor.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Give your eyes no sleepand your eyelids no slumber;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'save yourself like a gazelle from the hand of the hunter,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        like a bird from the hand of the fowler.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Go to the ant, O sluggard;consider her ways, and be wise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  Without having any chief,  officer, or ruler,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'she prepares her bread in summerand gathers her food in harvest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  How long will you lie there, O sluggard?When will you arise from
        your sleep?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  A little sleep, a little slumber,  a little folding of the hands
        to rest,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  and poverty will come upon you like a robber,and want like an armed
        man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  A worthless person, a wicked man,goes about with crooked speech,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  winks with his eyes, signals[[COMMENT(0)]] with his feet,points
        with his finger,  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'with perverted heart devises evil,continually sowing discord;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'therefore calamity will come upon him suddenly;  in a moment he will
        be broken beyond healing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'There are six things that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> hates, 
        seven that are an abomination to him:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  haughty eyes, a lying tongue,and hands that shed innocent blood,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  a heart that devises wicked plans,  feet that make haste to run
        to evil,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Warnings Against Adultery'
      title: Warnings Against Adultery
      number: 19
      content: '  a false witness who breathes out lies,and one who sows discord
        among brothers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  My son, keep your father\u2019s commandment,  and forsake not your
        mother\u2019s teaching.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Bind them on your heart always;  tie them around your neck.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  When you walk, they[[COMMENT(0)]] will lead you;  when you lie
        down, they will watch over you;and when you awake, they will talk with you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:22 '
        content: Hebrew ; three times in this verse
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For the commandment is a lamp and the teaching a light,and the reproofs
        of discipline are the way of life,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'to preserve you from the evil woman,[[COMMENT(0)]]from the smooth
        tongue of the adulteress.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:24 '
        content: 'Revocalization (compare Septuagint) yields Hebrew '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  Do not desire her beauty in your heart,and do not let her capture
        you with her eyelashes;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'for the price of a prostitute is only a loaf of bread,[[COMMENT(0)]]but
        a married woman  hunts down a precious life.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:26 '
        content: 'Or (compare Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate) Hebrew '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Can a man carry fire next to his chestand his clothes not be burned?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Or can one walk on hot coalsand his feet not be scorched?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "So is he who goes in to his neighbor\u2019s wife;none who touches
        her will go unpunished.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'People do not despise a thief if he stealsto satisfy his appetite
        when he is hungry,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'but if he is caught, he will pay sevenfold;he will give all the goods
        of his house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He who commits adultery lacks sense;he who does it destroys himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He will get wounds and dishonor,and his disgrace will not be wiped
        away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'For jealousy makes a man furious,and he will not spare when he takes
        revenge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: He will accept no compensation;he will refuse though you multiply
        gifts.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Warning Against the Adulteress'
      title: Warning Against the Adulteress
      number: 1
      content: '    My son, keep my wordsand treasure up my commandments with you;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  keep my commandments and live;keep my teaching as the apple of
        your eye;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  bind them on your fingers;  write them on the tablet of your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Say to wisdom, \u201CYou are my sister,\u201Dand call insight your
        intimate friend,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'to keep you from the forbidden[[COMMENT(0)]] woman,from the adulteress
        with her smooth words.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For at the window of my houseI have looked out through my lattice,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and I have seen among the simple,I have perceived among the youths,a
        young man lacking sense,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'passing along the street near her corner,taking the road to her house  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'in the twilight, in the evening,at the time of night and darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And behold, the woman meets him,  dressed as a prostitute, wily of
        heart.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:10 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'She is loud and wayward;  her feet do not stay at home;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'now in the street, now in the market,and at every corner she lies
        in wait.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'She seizes him and kisses him,and with bold face she says to him,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CI had to offer sacrifices,[[COMMENT(0)]]and today I have paid
        my vows;  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'so now I have come out to meet you,to seek you eagerly, and I have
        found you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I have spread my couch with coverings,colored linens from Egyptian
        linen;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'I have perfumed my bed with myrrh,aloes, and cinnamon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Come, let us take our fill of love till morning;let us delight ourselves
        with love.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For my husband is not at home;he has gone on a long journey;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "he took a bag of money with him;at full moon he will come home.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'With much seductive speech she persuades him;with her smooth talk
        she compels him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'All at once he follows her,as an ox goes to the slaughter,or as a
        stag is caught fast[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:22 '
        content: 'Probable reading (compare Septuagint, Vulgate, Syriac); Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'till an arrow pierces its liver;as a bird rushes into a snare;he
        does not know that it will cost him his life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And now, O sons, listen to me,and be attentive to the words of my
        mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Let not your heart turn aside to her ways;do not stray into her paths,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'for many a victim has she laid low,and all her slain are a mighty
        throng.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Her house is the way to Sheol,going down to the chambers of death.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Blessings of Wisdom'
      title: The Blessings of Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: '  Does not wisdom call?Does not understanding raise her voice?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'On the heights beside the way,at the crossroads she takes her stand;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'beside the gates in front of the town,at the entrance of the portals
        she cries aloud:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CTo you, O men, I call,and my cry is to the children of man.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'O simple ones, learn prudence;O fools, learn sense.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Hear, for I will speak noble things,and from my lips will come what
        is right,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'for my mouth will utter truth;wickedness is an abomination to my
        lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'All the words of my mouth are righteous;there is nothing twisted
        or crooked in them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They are all straight to him who understands,and right to those who
        find knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Take my instruction instead of silver,and knowledge rather than
        choice gold,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  for wisdom is better than jewels,and all that you may desire cannot
        compare with her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI, wisdom, dwell with prudence,and I find knowledge and discretion.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  The fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is hatred of evil. 
        Pride and arrogance and the way of eviland perverted speech I hate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I have counsel and sound wisdom;I have insight; I have strength.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'By me kings reign,and rulers decree what is just;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'by me princes rule,and nobles, all who govern justly.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:16 '
        content: 'Most Hebrew manuscripts; many Hebrew manuscripts, Septuagint '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  I love those who love me,and those who seek me diligently find
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Riches and honor are with me,  enduring wealth and righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'My fruit is better than gold, even fine gold,and my yield than choice
        silver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I walk in the way of righteousness,in the paths of justice,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'granting an inheritance to those who love me,and filling their treasuries.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  possessed[[COMMENT(0)]]
        me at the beginning of his work,the first of his acts of old.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:22 '
        content: 'Or ; Septuagint Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Ages ago I was set up,at the first, before the beginning of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When there were no depths I was brought forth,when there were no
        springs abounding with water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Before the mountains had been shaped,  before the hills, I was brought
        forth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'before he had made the earth with its fields,or the first of the
        dust of the world.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'When he established the heavens, I was there;when he drew a circle
        on the face of the deep,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'when he made firm the skies above,when he established[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the fountains of the deep,  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:28 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'when he assigned to the sea its limit,so that the waters might not
        transgress his command,when he marked out the foundations of the earth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'then I was beside him, like a master workman,and I was daily his[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        delight,rejoicing before him always,  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:30 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  rejoicing in his inhabited worldand delighting in the children
        of man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CAnd now, O sons, listen to me:  blessed are those who keep
        my ways.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '  Hear instruction and be wise,and do not neglect it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '  Blessed is the one who listens to me,watching daily at my gates,waiting
        beside my doors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'For whoever finds me finds lifeand obtains favor from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "but he who fails to find me injures himself;all who hate me love
        death.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Way of Wisdom'
      title: The Way of Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: '    Wisdom has built her house;she has hewn her seven pillars.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'She has slaughtered her beasts; she has mixed her wine;she has also
        set her table.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'She has sent out her young women to callfrom the highest places in
        the town,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "  \u201CWhoever is simple, let him turn in here!\u201D  To him who
        lacks sense she says,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CCome, eat of my breadand drink of the wine I have mixed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Leave your simple ways,[[COMMENT(0)]] and live,  and walk in the
        way of insight.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Whoever corrects a scoffer gets himself abuse,and he who reproves
        a wicked man incurs injury.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Do not reprove a scoffer, or he will hate you;  reprove a wise
        man, and he will love you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Give instruction[[COMMENT(0)]] to a wise man, and he will be still
        wiser;teach a righteous man, and he will increase in learning.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:9 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  The fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is the beginning of
        wisdom,and the knowledge of the Holy One is insight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For by me your days will be multiplied,and years will be added to
        your life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Way of Folly'
      title: The Way of Folly
      number: 12
      content: '  If you are wise, you are wise for yourself;if you scoff, you alone
        will bear it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  The woman Folly is loud;she is seductive[[COMMENT(0)]] and knows
        nothing.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'She sits at the door of her house;she takes a seat on the highest
        places of the town,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'calling to those who pass by,who are going straight on their way,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  \u201CWhoever is simple, let him turn in here!\u201DAnd to him
        who lacks sense she says,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "  \u201CStolen water is sweet,and bread eaten in secret is pleasant.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: But he does not know that the dead[[COMMENT(0)]] are there,that her
        guests are in the depths of Sheol.
      comments:
      - number: '9:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Proverbs of Solomon'
      title: The Proverbs of Solomon
      number: 1
      content: '    The proverbs of Solomon.  A wise son makes a glad father,  but
        a foolish son is a sorrow to his mother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Treasures gained by wickedness do not profit,  but righteousness
        delivers from death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> does not let the righteous go hungry, 
        but he thwarts the craving of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'A slack hand causes poverty,  but the hand of the diligent makes
        rich.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He who gathers in summer is a prudent son,but he who sleeps in harvest
        is a son who brings shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Blessings are on the head of the righteous,but the mouth of the wicked
        conceals violence.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:6 '
        content: Or ; also verse 11
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The memory of the righteous is a blessing,but the name of the wicked
        will rot.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  The wise of heart will receive commandments,but a babbling fool
        will come to ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Whoever walks in integrity walks securely,but he who makes his
        ways crooked will be found out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Whoever winks the eye causes trouble,and a babbling fool will come
        to ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  The mouth of the righteous is a fountain of life,but the mouth
        of the wicked conceals violence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Hatred stirs up strife,but love covers all offenses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'On the lips of him who has understanding, wisdom is found,but a rod
        is for the back of him who lacks sense.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The wise lay up knowledge,but the mouth of a fool brings ruin near.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  A rich man\u2019s wealth is his strong city;the poverty of the
        poor is their ruin.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The wage of the righteous leads to life,the gain of the wicked to
        sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Whoever heeds instruction is on the path to life,but he who rejects
        reproof leads others astray.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The one who conceals hatred has lying lips,and whoever utters slander
        is a fool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  When words are many, transgression is not lacking,  but whoever
        restrains his lips is prudent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The tongue of the righteous is choice silver;the heart of the wicked
        is of little worth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The lips of the righteous feed many,but fools die for lack of sense.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  The blessing of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> makes rich,and
        he adds no sorrow with it.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:22 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Doing wrong is like a joke to a fool,but wisdom is pleasure to a
        man of understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  What the wicked dreads will come upon him,but the desire of the
        righteous will be granted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When the tempest passes, the wicked is no more,but the righteous
        is established forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Like vinegar to the teeth and smoke to the eyes,so is the sluggard
        to those who send him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  The fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> prolongs life,  but
        the years of the wicked will be short.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  The hope of the righteous brings joy,  but the expectation of the
        wicked will perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  The way of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is a stronghold to the
        blameless,but destruction to evildoers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  The righteous will never be removed,but the wicked will not dwell
        in the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  The mouth of the righteous brings forth wisdom,but the perverse
        tongue will be cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: The lips of the righteous know what is acceptable,but the mouth of
        the wicked, what is perverse.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    A false balance is an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        but a just weight is his delight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  When pride comes, then comes disgrace,but with the humble is wisdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  The integrity of the upright guides them,  but the crookedness
        of the treacherous destroys them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Riches do not profit in the day of wrath,  but righteousness delivers
        from death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The righteousness of the blameless keeps his way straight,but the
        wicked falls by his own wickedness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The righteousness of the upright delivers them,but the treacherous
        are taken captive by their lust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When the wicked dies, his hope will perish,and the expectation of
        wealth[[COMMENT(0)]] perishes too.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:7 '
        content: 'Or , or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  The righteous is delivered from trouble,and the wicked walks into
        it instead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'With his mouth the godless man would destroy his neighbor,but by
        knowledge the righteous are delivered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  When it goes well with the righteous, the city rejoices,and when
        the wicked perish there are shouts of gladness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'By the blessing of the upright a city is exalted,but by the mouth
        of the wicked it is overthrown.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Whoever belittles his neighbor lacks sense,but a man of understanding
        remains silent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Whoever goes about slandering reveals secrets,but he who is trustworthy
        in spirit keeps a thing covered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Where there is no guidance, a people falls,  but in an abundance
        of counselors there is safety.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Whoever puts up security for a stranger will surely suffer harm,but
        he who hates striking hands in pledge is secure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  A gracious woman gets honor,and violent men get riches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  A man who is kind benefits himself,but a cruel man hurts himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The wicked earns deceptive wages,but one who sows righteousness gets
        a sure reward.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Whoever is steadfast in righteousness will live,but he who pursues
        evil will die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Those of crooked heart are an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,but
        those of blameless ways are his delight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Be assured, an evil person will not go unpunished,but the offspring
        of the righteous will be delivered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Like a gold ring in a pig\u2019s snoutis a beautiful woman without
        discretion.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The desire of the righteous ends only in good,  the expectation of
        the wicked in wrath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  One gives freely, yet grows all the richer;another withholds what
        he should give, and only suffers want.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  Whoever brings blessing will be enriched,and one who waters will
        himself be watered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  The people curse him who holds back grain,but a blessing is on
        the head of him who sells it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Whoever diligently seeks good seeks favor,[[COMMENT(0)]]but evil
        comes to him who searches for it.  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:27 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Whoever trusts in his riches will fall,but the righteous will flourish
        like a green leaf.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Whoever troubles his own household will inherit the wind,and the
        fool will be servant to the wise of heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The fruit of the righteous is a tree of life,and whoever captures
        souls is wise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: If the righteous is repaid on earth,how much more the wicked and the
        sinner!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Whoever loves discipline loves knowledge,but he who hates reproof
        is stupid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A good man obtains favor from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,but
        a man of evil devices he condemns.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'No one is established by wickedness,but the root of the righteous
        will never be moved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  An excellent wife is the crown of her husband,but she who brings
        shame is like rottenness in his bones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  The thoughts of the righteous are just;the counsels of the wicked
        are deceitful.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The words of the wicked lie in wait for blood,but the mouth of the
        upright delivers them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The wicked are overthrown and are no more,  but the house of the
        righteous will stand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'A man is commended according to his good sense,but one of twisted
        mind is despised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Better to be lowly and have a servantthan to play the great man and
        lack bread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Whoever is righteous has regard for the life of his beast,but the
        mercy of the wicked is cruel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Whoever works his land will have plenty of bread,  but he who follows
        worthless pursuits lacks sense.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Whoever is wicked covets the spoil of evildoers,but the root of the
        righteous bears fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'An evil man is ensnared by the transgression of his lips,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        but the righteous escapes from trouble.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:13 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "From the fruit of his mouth a man is satisfied with good,  and the
        work of a man\u2019s hand comes back to him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  The way of a fool is right in his own eyes,but a wise man listens
        to advice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  The vexation of a fool is known at once,but the prudent ignores
        an insult.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Whoever speaks[[COMMENT(0)]] the truth gives honest evidence,but
        a false witness utters deceit.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:17 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  There is one whose rash words are like sword thrusts,but the tongue
        of the wise brings healing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Truthful lips endure forever,but a lying tongue is but for a moment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Deceit is in the heart of those who devise evil,but those who plan
        peace have joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  No ill befalls the righteous,but the wicked are filled with trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  Lying lips are an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        but those who act faithfully are his delight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  A prudent man conceals knowledge,  but the heart of fools proclaims
        folly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  The hand of the diligent will rule,while the slothful will be put
        to forced labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  Anxiety in a man\u2019s heart weighs him down,but a good word makes
        him glad.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'One who is righteous is a guide to his neighbor,[[COMMENT(0)]]but
        the way of the wicked leads them astray.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:26 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  Whoever is slothful will not roast his game,but the diligent man
        will get precious wealth.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:27 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  In the path of righteousness is life,and in its pathway there is
        no death.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  A wise son hears his father\u2019s instruction,but a scoffer does
        not listen to rebuke.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'From the fruit of his mouth a man eats what is good,but the desire
        of the treacherous is for violence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Whoever guards his mouth preserves his life;  he who opens wide
        his lips comes to ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  The soul of the sluggard craves and gets nothing,while the soul
        of the diligent is richly supplied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The righteous hates falsehood,but the wicked brings shame[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and disgrace.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:5 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Righteousness guards him whose way is blameless,but sin overthrows
        the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  One pretends to be rich,[[COMMENT(0)]] yet has nothing;  another
        pretends to be poor, yet has great wealth.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:7 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The ransom of a man\u2019s life is his wealth,but a poor man hears
        no threat.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  The light of the righteous rejoices,but the lamp of the wicked
        will be put out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  By insolence comes nothing but strife,but with those who take advice
        is wisdom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Wealth gained hastily[[COMMENT(0)]] will dwindle,but whoever gathers
        little by little will increase it.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Hope deferred makes the heart sick,  but a desire fulfilled is a
        tree of life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Whoever despises the word[[COMMENT(0)]] brings destruction on himself,but
        he who reveres the commandment will be rewarded.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:13 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The teaching of the wise is a fountain of life,that one may turn
        away from the snares of death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Good sense wins favor,but the way of the treacherous is their ruin.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:15 '
        content: 'Probable reading (compare Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate); Hebrew
          , or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  Every prudent man acts with knowledge,  but a fool flaunts his
        folly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'A wicked messenger falls into trouble,but a faithful envoy brings
        healing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Poverty and disgrace come to him who ignores instruction,  but whoever
        heeds reproof is honored.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  A desire fulfilled is sweet to the soul,but to turn away from evil
        is an abomination to fools.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Whoever walks with the wise becomes wise,but the companion of fools
        will suffer harm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Disaster[[COMMENT(0)]] pursues sinners,  but the righteous are
        rewarded with good.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:21 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  A good man leaves an inheritance to his children\u2019s children,but
        the sinner\u2019s wealth is laid up for the righteous.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The fallow ground of the poor would yield much food,but it is swept
        away through injustice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  Whoever spares the rod hates his son,but he who loves him is diligent
        to discipline him.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:24 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  The righteous has enough to satisfy his appetite,but the belly
        of the wicked suffers want.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    The wisest of women builds her house,but folly with her own hands
        tears it down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Whoever walks in uprightness fears the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,but
        he who is devious in his ways despises him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'By the mouth of a fool comes a rod for his back,[[COMMENT(0)]]  but
        the lips of the wise will preserve them.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:3 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Where there are no oxen, the manger is clean,but abundant crops come
        by the strength of the ox.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  A faithful witness does not lie,but a false witness breathes out
        lies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  A scoffer seeks wisdom in vain,but knowledge is easy for a man
        of understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Leave the presence of a fool,for there you do not meet words of knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The wisdom of the prudent is to discern his way,but the folly of
        fools is deceiving.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Fools mock at the guilt offering,but the upright enjoy acceptance.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:9 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The heart knows its own bitterness,and no stranger shares its joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  The house of the wicked will be destroyed,but the tent of the upright
        will flourish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  There is a way that seems right to a man,but its end is the way
        to death.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:12 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Even in laughter the heart may ache,and the end of joy may be grief.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The backslider in heart will be filled with the fruit of his ways,and
        a good man will be filled with the fruit of his ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  The simple believes everything,but the prudent gives thought to
        his steps.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  One who is wise is cautious[[COMMENT(0)]]<smallcaps> and </smallcaps>turns
        away from evil,but a fool is reckless and careless.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:16 '
        content: Or [the <span class="ChapterContent_nd__ECPAf">Lord</span>]
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'A man of quick temper acts foolishly,and a man of evil devices is
        hated.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The simple inherit folly,but the prudent are crowned with knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  The evil bow down before the good,the wicked at the gates of the
        righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  The poor is disliked even by his neighbor,  but the rich has many
        friends.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Whoever despises his neighbor is a sinner,but blessed is he who is
        generous to the poor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Do they not go astray who devise evil?Those who devise good meet[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        steadfast love and faithfulness.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:22 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In all toil there is profit,but mere talk tends only to poverty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The crown of the wise is their wealth,but the folly of fools brings
        folly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'A truthful witness saves lives,but one who breathes out lies is deceitful.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'In the fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> one has strong confidence,and
        his children will have a refuge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is a fountain of life,that
        one may turn away from the snares of death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'In a multitude of people is the glory of a king,but without people
        a prince is ruined.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Whoever is slow to anger has great understanding,but he who has a
        hasty temper exalts folly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'A tranquil[[COMMENT(0)]] heart gives life to the flesh,but envy makes
        the bones rot.  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:30 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Whoever oppresses a poor man insults his Maker,  but he who is generous
        to the needy honors him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '  The wicked is overthrown through his evildoing,but the righteous
        finds refuge in his death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Wisdom rests in the heart of a man of understanding,but it makes
        itself known even in the midst of fools.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '14:33 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Righteousness exalts a nation,but sin is a reproach to any people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "A servant who deals wisely has the king\u2019s favor,but his wrath
        falls on one who acts shamefully."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    A soft answer turns away wrath,but a harsh word stirs up anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The tongue of the wise commends knowledge,but the mouths of fools
        pour out folly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  The eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> are in every place,keeping
        watch on the evil and the good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  A gentle[[COMMENT(0)]] tongue is a tree of life,but perverseness
        in it breaks the spirit.  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "  A fool despises his father\u2019s instruction,but whoever heeds
        reproof is prudent.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In the house of the righteous there is much treasure,but trouble
        befalls the income of the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The lips of the wise spread knowledge;  not so the hearts of fools.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:7 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,but
        the prayer of the upright is acceptable to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The way of the wicked is an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,but
        he loves him who pursues righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'There is severe discipline for him who forsakes the way;  whoever
        hates reproof will die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Sheol and Abaddon lie open before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;how
        much more the hearts of the children of man!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  A scoffer does not like to be reproved;he will not go to the wise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  A glad heart makes a cheerful face,but by sorrow of heart the spirit
        is crushed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  The heart of him who has understanding seeks knowledge,but the
        mouths of fools feed on folly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'All the days of the afflicted are evil,but the cheerful of heart
        has a continual feast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  Better is a little with the fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>than
        great treasure and trouble with it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Better is a dinner of herbs where love isthan a fattened ox and
        hatred with it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  A hot-tempered man stirs up strife,but he who is slow to anger
        quiets contention.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The way of a sluggard is like a hedge of thorns,but the path of the
        upright is a level highway.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  A wise son makes a glad father,but a foolish man despises his mother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Folly is a joy to him who lacks sense,but a man of understanding
        walks straight ahead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  Without counsel plans fail,but with many advisers they succeed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'To make an apt answer is a joy to a man,and a word in season, how
        good it is!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The path of life leads upward for the prudent,that he may turn away
        from Sheol beneath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> tears down the house of the proudbut
        maintains the widow\u2019s boundaries.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  The thoughts of the wicked are an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,but
        gracious words are pure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Whoever is greedy for unjust gain troubles his own household,but
        he who hates bribes will live.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The heart of the righteous ponders how to answer,but the mouth of
        the wicked pours out evil things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is far from the wicked,but he hears
        the prayer of the righteous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  The light of the eyes rejoices the heart,and good news refreshes[[COMMENT(0)]]
        the bones.  '
      comments:
      - number: '15:30 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  The ear that listens to life-giving reproofwill dwell among the
        wise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Whoever ignores instruction despises himself,but he who listens to
        reproof gains intelligence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '  The fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is instruction in wisdom,and
        humility comes before honor.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  The plans of the heart belong to man,but the answer of the tongue
        is from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  All the ways of a man are pure in his own eyes,but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        weighs the spirit.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Commit your work to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and your plans
        will be established.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has made everything for its purpose,even
        the wicked for the day of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Everyone who is arrogant in heart is an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; 
        be assured, he will not go unpunished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'By steadfast love and faithfulness iniquity is atoned for,and by
        the fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> one turns away from evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When a man\u2019s ways please the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,  he
        makes even his enemies to be at peace with him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Better is a little with righteousnessthan great revenues with injustice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  The heart of man plans his way,but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        establishes his steps.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  An oracle is on the lips of a king;his mouth does not sin in judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  A just balance and scales are the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s;all
        the weights in the bag are his work.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'It is an abomination to kings to do evil,for the throne is established
        by righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Righteous lips are the delight of a king,and he loves him who speaks
        what is right.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  A king\u2019s wrath is a messenger of death,and a wise man will
        appease it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "  In the light of a king\u2019s face there is life,and his favor
        is like the clouds that bring the spring rain.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  How much better to get wisdom than gold!To get understanding is
        to be chosen rather than silver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The highway of the upright turns aside from evil;whoever guards his
        way preserves his life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Pride goes before destruction,and a haughty spirit before a fall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  It is better to be of a lowly spirit with the poorthan to divide
        the spoil with the proud.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Whoever gives thought to the word[[COMMENT(0)]]  will discover good,and
        blessed is he who trusts in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:20 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The wise of heart is called discerning,and sweetness of speech increases
        persuasiveness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Good sense is a fountain of life to him who has it,but the instruction
        of fools is folly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  The heart of the wise makes his speech judiciousand adds persuasiveness
        to his lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  Gracious words are like a honeycomb,sweetness to the soul and health
        to the body.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'There is a way that seems right to a man,but its end is the way to
        death.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:25 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "A worker\u2019s appetite works for him;his mouth urges him on.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  A worthless man plots evil,and his speech[[COMMENT(0)]] is like
        a scorching fire.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:27 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  A dishonest man spreads strife,and a whisperer separates close
        friends.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'A man of violence entices his neighborand leads him in a way that
        is not good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Whoever winks his eyes plans[[COMMENT(0)]]  dishonest things;he who
        purses his lips brings evil to pass.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:30 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  Gray hair is a crown of glory;it is gained in a righteous life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '  Whoever is slow to anger is better than the mighty,and he who rules
        his spirit than he who takes a city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '  The lot is cast into the lap,but its every decision is from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    Better is a dry morsel with quietthan a house full of feasting[[COMMENT(0)]]
        with strife.  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:1 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A servant who deals wisely will rule over a son who acts shamefullyand
        will share the inheritance as one of the brothers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  The crucible is for silver, and the furnace is for gold,  and the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> tests hearts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'An evildoer listens to wicked lips,and a liar gives ear to a mischievous
        tongue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Whoever mocks the poor insults his Maker;he who is glad at calamity
        will not go unpunished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Grandchildren are the crown of the aged,and the glory of children
        is their fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Fine speech is not becoming to a fool;still less is false speech
        to a prince.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  A bribe is like a magic[[COMMENT(0)]] stone in the eyes of the
        one who gives it;wherever he turns he prospers.  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Whoever covers an offense seeks love,but he who repeats a matter
        separates close friends.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'A rebuke goes deeper into a man of understandingthan a hundred blows
        into a fool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'An evil man seeks only rebellion,and a cruel messenger will be sent
        against him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Let a man meet a she-bear robbed of her cubs  rather than a fool
        in his folly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'If anyone returns evil for good,  evil will not depart from his house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The beginning of strife is like letting out water,so quit before
        the quarrel breaks out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He who justifies the wicked and he who condemns the righteousare
        both alike an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Why should a fool have money in his hand to buy wisdomwhen he has
        no sense?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  A friend loves at all times,and a brother is born for adversity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'One who lacks sense gives a pledgeand puts up security in the presence
        of his neighbor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Whoever loves transgression loves strife;he who makes his door high
        seeks destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  A man of crooked heart does not discover good,and one with a dishonest
        tongue falls into calamity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He who sires a fool gets himself sorrow,and the father of a fool
        has no joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  A joyful heart is good medicine,but a crushed spirit dries up the
        bones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The wicked accepts a bribe in secret[[COMMENT(0)]]to pervert the
        ways of justice.  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:23 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  The discerning sets his face toward wisdom,but the eyes of a fool
        are on the ends of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  A foolish son is a grief to his father  and bitterness to her who
        bore him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  To impose a fine on a righteous man is not good,nor to strike the
        noble for their uprightness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Whoever restrains his words has knowledge,and he who has a cool spirit
        is a man of understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Even a fool who keeps silent is considered wise;when he closes his
        lips, he is deemed intelligent.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Whoever isolates himself seeks his own desire;he breaks out against
        all sound judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'A fool takes no pleasure in understanding,but only in expressing
        his opinion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When wickedness comes, contempt comes also,and with dishonor comes
        disgrace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "The words of a man\u2019s mouth are deep waters;the fountain of wisdom
        is a bubbling brook.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'It is not good to be partial to[[COMMENT(0)]] the wickedor to deprive
        the righteous of justice.  '
      comments:
      - number: '18:5 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "A fool\u2019s lips walk into a fight,and his mouth invites a beating.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  A fool\u2019s mouth is his ruin,and his lips are a snare to his
        soul.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  The words of a whisperer are like delicious morsels;they go down
        into the inner parts of the body.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Whoever is slack in his workis a brother to him who destroys.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  The name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is a strong tower;the
        righteous man runs into it and is safe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "  A rich man\u2019s wealth is his strong city,and like a high wall
        in his imagination.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  Before destruction a man\u2019s heart is haughty,but humility comes
        before honor.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'If one gives an answer before he hears,it is his folly and shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "A man\u2019s spirit will endure sickness,but a crushed spirit who
        can bear?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'An intelligent heart acquires knowledge,and the ear of the wise seeks
        knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "A man\u2019s gift makes room for himand brings him before the great.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The one who states his case first seems right,until the other comes
        and examines him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  The lot puts an end to quarrelsand decides between powerful contenders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'A brother offended is more unyielding than a strong city,and quarreling
        is like the bars of a castle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  From the fruit of a man\u2019s mouth his stomach is satisfied;he
        is satisfied by the yield of his lips.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Death and life are in the power of the tongue,and those who love
        it will eat its fruits.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He who finds a wife finds a good thingand obtains favor from the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The poor use entreaties,but the rich answer roughly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: A man of many companions may come to ruin,but there is a friend who
        sticks closer than a brother.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    Better is a poor person who walks in his integritythan one who
        is crooked in speech and is a fool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Desire[[COMMENT(0)]] without knowledge is not good,and whoever makes
        haste with his feet misses his way.  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "When a man\u2019s folly brings his way to ruin,his heart rages against
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Wealth brings many new friends,  but a poor man is deserted by
        his friend.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  A false witness will not go unpunished,and he who breathes out
        lies will not escape.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Many seek the favor of a generous man,[[COMMENT(0)]]and everyone
        is a friend to a man who gives gifts.  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:6 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "  All a poor man\u2019s brothers hate him;  how much more do his
        friends go far from him!He pursues them with words, but does not have them.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '19:7 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew sentence is uncertain
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Whoever gets sense loves his own soul;he who keeps understanding
        will discover good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  A false witness will not go unpunished,and he who breathes out
        lies will perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  It is not fitting for a fool to live in luxury,much less for a
        slave to rule over princes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Good sense makes one slow to anger,and it is his glory to overlook
        an offense.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "A king\u2019s wrath is like the growling of a lion,but his favor
        is like dew on the grass.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  A foolish son is ruin to his father,and a wife\u2019s quarreling
        is a continual dripping of rain.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  House and wealth are inherited from fathers,but a prudent wife
        is from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Slothfulness casts into a deep sleep,and an idle person will suffer
        hunger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Whoever keeps the commandment keeps his life;he who despises his
        ways will die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Whoever is generous to the poor lends to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        he will repay him for his deed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Discipline your son, for there is hope;do not set your heart on
        putting him to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'A man of great wrath will pay the penalty,for if you deliver him,
        you will only have to do it again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Listen to advice and accept instruction,that you may gain wisdom
        in the future.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  Many are the plans in the mind of a man,but it is the purpose of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  that will stand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'What is desired in a man is steadfast love,and a poor man is better
        than a liar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  leads to life,and whoever
        has it rests satisfied;he will not be visited by harm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  The sluggard buries his hand in the dishand will not even bring
        it back to his mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  Strike a scoffer, and the simple will learn prudence;  reprove
        a man of understanding, and he will gain knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He who does violence to his father and chases away his motheris a
        son who brings shame and reproach.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Cease to hear instruction, my son,  and you will stray from the words
        of knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'A worthless witness mocks at justice,and the mouth of the wicked
        devours iniquity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Condemnation is ready for scoffers,and beating for the backs of fools.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    Wine is a mocker, strong drink a brawler,and whoever is led astray
        by it is not wise.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:1 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The terror of a king is like the growling of a lion;whoever provokes
        him to anger forfeits his life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It is an honor for a man to keep aloof from strife,but every fool
        will be quarreling.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  The sluggard does not plow in the autumn;  he will seek at harvest
        and have nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The purpose in a man\u2019s heart is like deep water,but a man of
        understanding will draw it out.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Many a man proclaims his own steadfast love,but a faithful man who
        can find?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The righteous who walks in his integrity\u2014  blessed are his children
        after him!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  A king who sits on the throne of judgment  winnows all evil with
        his eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  Who can say, \u201CI have made my heart pure;I am clean from my
        sin\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Unequal[[COMMENT(0)]] weights and unequal measuresare both alike
        an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:10 '
        content: Or ; also verse 23
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Even a child makes himself known by his acts,by whether his conduct
        is pure and upright.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  The hearing ear and the seeing eye,  the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has made them both.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Love not sleep, lest you come to poverty;open your eyes, and you
        will have plenty of bread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CBad, bad,\u201D says the buyer,but when he goes away, then
        he boasts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'There is gold and abundance of costly stones,  but the lips of knowledge
        are a precious jewel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  Take a man\u2019s garment when he has put up security for a stranger,and
        hold it in pledge when he puts up security for foreigners.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '20:16 '
        content: Or (compare 27:13)
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Bread gained by deceit is sweet to a man,but afterward his mouth
        will be full of gravel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Plans are established by counsel;by wise guidance wage war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Whoever goes about slandering reveals secrets;therefore do not associate
        with a simple babbler.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:19 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  If one curses his father or his mother,  his lamp will be put out
        in utter darkness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  An inheritance gained hastily in the beginningwill not be blessed
        in the end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Do not say, \u201CI will repay evil\u201D;  wait for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and he will deliver you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Unequal weights are an abomination to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,and
        false scales are not good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "A man\u2019s steps are from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;how then
        can man understand his way?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "It is a snare to say rashly, \u201CIt is holy,\u201Dand to reflect
        only after making vows.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'A wise king winnows the wickedand drives the wheel over them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  The spirit[[COMMENT(0)]] of man is the lamp of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, 
        searching all his innermost parts.  '
      comments:
      - number: '20:27 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  Steadfast love and faithfulness preserve the king,and by steadfast
        love his throne is upheld.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'The glory of young men is their strength,but the splendor of old
        men is their gray hair.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  Blows that wound cleanse away evil;strokes make clean the innermost
        parts.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "  The king\u2019s heart is a stream of water in the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>;he
        turns it wherever he will.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  Every way of a man is right in his own eyes,but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        weighs the heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  To do righteousness and justiceis more acceptable to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        than sacrifice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Haughty eyes and a proud heart,  the lamp[[COMMENT(0)]] of the
        wicked, are sin.  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The plans of the diligent lead surely to abundance,but everyone who
        is hasty comes only to poverty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  The getting of treasures by a lying tongueis a fleeting vapor and
        a snare of death.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:6 '
        content: 'Some Hebrew manuscripts, Septuagint, Latin; most Hebrew manuscripts '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The violence of the wicked will sweep them away,because they refuse
        to do what is just.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The way of the guilty is crooked,but the conduct of the pure is upright.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'It is better to live in a corner of the housetopthan in a house shared
        with a quarrelsome wife.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The soul of the wicked desires evil;his neighbor finds no mercy in
        his eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When a scoffer is punished, the simple becomes wise;when a wise man
        is instructed, he gains knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The Righteous One observes the house of the wicked;he throws the
        wicked down to ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '  Whoever closes his ear to the cry of the poorwill himself call
        out and not be answered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  A gift in secret averts anger,and a concealed bribe,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        strong wrath.  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'When justice is done, it is a joy to the righteous  but terror to
        evildoers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'One who wanders from the way of good sense  will rest in the assembly
        of the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Whoever loves pleasure will be a poor man;he who loves wine and oil
        will not be rich.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  The wicked is a ransom for the righteous,and the traitor for the
        upright.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'It is better to live in a desert landthan with a quarrelsome and
        fretful woman.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "  Precious treasure and oil are in a wise man\u2019s dwelling,but
        a foolish man devours it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Whoever pursues righteousness and kindnesswill find life, righteousness,
        and honor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  A wise man scales the city of the mightyand brings down the stronghold
        in which they trust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Whoever keeps his mouth and his tongue  keeps himself out of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "  \u201CScoffer\u201D is the name of the arrogant, haughty manwho
        acts with arrogant pride.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The desire of the sluggard kills him,for his hands refuse to labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'All day long he craves and craves,but the righteous gives and does
        not hold back.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination;how much more when
        he brings it with evil intent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  A false witness will perish,but the word of a man who hears will
        endure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'A wicked man puts on a bold face,but the upright gives thought to[[COMMENT(0)]]
        his ways.  '
      comments:
      - number: '21:29 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  No wisdom, no understanding, no counselcan avail against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  The horse is made ready for the day of battle,but the victory belongs
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    A good name is to be chosen rather than great riches,and favor
        is better than silver or gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: '  The rich and the poor meet together;the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is the Maker of them all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  The prudent sees danger and hides himself,but the simple go on
        and suffer for it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The reward for humility and fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>is
        riches and honor and life.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:4 '
        content: Or <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Thorns and snares are in the way of the crooked;whoever guards
        his soul will keep far from them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Train up a child in the way he should go;even when he is old he
        will not depart from it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The rich rules over the poor,and the borrower is the slave of the
        lender.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Whoever sows injustice will reap calamity,and the rod of his fury
        will fail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Whoever has a bountiful[[COMMENT(0)]] eye will be blessed,for he
        shares his bread with the poor.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:9 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Drive out a scoffer, and strife will go out,and quarreling and
        abuse will cease.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He who loves purity of heart,and whose speech is gracious, will have
        the king as his friend.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> keep watch over knowledge,but
        he overthrows the words of the traitor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  The sluggard says, \u201CThere is a lion outside!I shall be killed
        in the streets!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The mouth of forbidden[[COMMENT(0)]] women is a deep pit;  he with
        whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is angry will fall into it.  '
      comments:
      - number: '22:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Folly is bound up in the heart of a child,but the rod of discipline
        drives it far from him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Words of the Wise'
      title: Words of the Wise
      number: 16
      content: 'Whoever oppresses the poor to increase his own wealth,or gives to
        the rich, will only come to poverty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Incline your ear, and hear the words of the wise,  and apply your
        heart to my knowledge,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'for it will be pleasant if you keep them within you,if all of them
        are ready on your lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'That your trust may be in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,I have
        made them known to you today, even to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Have I not written for you thirty sayingsof counsel and knowledge,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'to make you know what is right and true,that you may give a true
        answer to those who sent you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  Do not rob the poor, because he is poor,or crush the afflicted
        at the gate,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will plead their causeand rob
        of life those who rob them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Make no friendship with a man given to anger,nor go with a wrathful
        man,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'lest you learn his waysand entangle yourself in a snare.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Be not one of those who give pledges,who put up security for debts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'If you have nothing with which to pay,why should your bed be taken
        from under you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Do not move the ancient landmarkthat your fathers have set.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: Do you see a man skillful in his work?He will stand before kings;he
        will not stand before obscure men.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  When you sit down to eat with a ruler,observe carefully what[[COMMENT(0)]]
        is before you,  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:1 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and put a knife to your throatif you are given to appetite.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Do not desire his delicacies,for they are deceptive food.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Do not toil to acquire wealth;  be discerning enough to desist.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When your eyes light on it, it is gone,  for suddenly it sprouts
        wings,flying like an eagle toward heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Do not eat the bread of a man who is stingy;[[COMMENT(0)]]  do
        not desire his delicacies,  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "for he is like one who is inwardly calculating.[[COMMENT(0)]]\u201CEat
        and drink!\u201D he says to you,but his heart is not with you.  "
      comments:
      - number: '23:7 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You will vomit up the morsels that you have eaten,and waste your
        pleasant words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not speak in the hearing of a fool,for he will despise the good
        sense of your words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Do not move an ancient landmarkor enter the fields of the fatherless,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'for their Redeemer is strong;he will plead their cause against you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Apply your heart to instructionand your ear to words of knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Do not withhold discipline from a child;  if you strike him with
        a rod, he will not die.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If you strike him with the rod,you will save his soul from Sheol.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  My son, if your heart is wise,my heart too will be glad.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'My inmost being[[COMMENT(0)]] will exultwhen your lips speak what
        is right.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Let not your heart envy sinners,but continue in the fear of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        all the day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Surely there is a future,and your hope will not be cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hear, my son, and be wise,and direct your heart in the way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Be not among drunkards[[COMMENT(0)]]or among gluttonous eaters of
        meat,  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:20 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'for the drunkard and the glutton will come to poverty,and slumber
        will clothe them with rags.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  Listen to your father who gave you life,  and do not despise your
        mother when she is old.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Buy truth, and do not sell it;buy wisdom, instruction, and understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  The father of the righteous will greatly rejoice;he who fathers
        a wise son will be glad in him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  Let your father and mother be glad;let her who bore you rejoice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'My son, give me your heart,and let your eyes observe[[COMMENT(0)]]
        my ways.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:26 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For a prostitute is a deep pit;  an adulteress[[COMMENT(0)]] is a
        narrow well.  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:27 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  She lies in wait like a robberand increases the traitors among
        mankind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  Who has woe? Who has sorrow?Who has strife? Who has complaining?Who
        has wounds without cause?Who has redness of eyes?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Those who tarry long over wine;those who go to try mixed wine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Do not look at wine when it is red,when it sparkles in the cupand
        goes down smoothly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'In the end it bites like a serpentand stings like an adder.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Your eyes will see strange things,and your heart utter perverse things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'You will be like one who lies down in the midst of the sea,like one
        who lies on the top of a mast.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '23:34 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "\u201CThey struck me,\u201D you will say,[[COMMENT(0)]] \u201Cbut
        I was not hurt;they beat me, but I did not feel it.When shall I awake?I must
        have another drink.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '23:35 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Be not envious of evil men,nor desire to be with them,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'for their hearts devise violence,and their lips talk of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'By wisdom a house is built,and by understanding it is established;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'by knowledge the rooms are filledwith all precious and pleasant riches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  A wise man is full of strength,and a man of knowledge enhances
        his might,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'for by wise guidance you can wage your war,and in abundance of counselors
        there is victory.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Wisdom is too high for a fool;in the gate he does not open his mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Whoever plans to do evilwill be called a schemer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  The devising[[COMMENT(0)]] of folly is sin,and the scoffer is an
        abomination to mankind.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'If you faint in the day of adversity,your strength is small.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Rescue those who are being taken away to death;hold back those
        who are stumbling to the slaughter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "If you say, \u201CBehold, we did not know this,\u201D  does not he
        who weighs the heart perceive it?Does not he who keeps watch over your soul
        know it,and will he not repay man according to his work?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'My son, eat honey, for it is good,and the drippings of the honeycomb
        are sweet to your taste.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Know that wisdom is such to your soul;if you find it, there will
        be a future,and your hope will not be cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  Lie not in wait as a wicked man against the dwelling of the righteous;do
        no violence to his home;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  for the righteous falls seven times and rises again,but the wicked
        stumble in times of calamity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Do not rejoice when your enemy falls,and let not your heart be
        glad when he stumbles,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'lest the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> see it and be displeased,and
        turn away his anger from him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Fret not yourself because of evildoers,and be not envious of the
        wicked,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'for the evil man has no future;  the lamp of the wicked will be put
        out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'My son, fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and the king,and do
        not join with those who do otherwise,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: More Sayings of the Wise'
      title: More Sayings of the Wise
      number: 22
      content: 'for disaster will arise suddenly from them,and who knows the ruin
        that will come from them both?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'These also are sayings of the wise.  Partiality in judging is not
        good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Whoever says to the wicked, \u201CYou are in the right,\u201D  will
        be cursed by peoples, abhorred by nations,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'but those who rebuke the wicked will have delight,and a good blessing
        will come upon them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Whoever gives an honest answerkisses the lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  Prepare your work outside;get everything ready for yourself in
        the field,and after that build your house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: '  Be not a witness against your neighbor without cause,and do not
        deceive with your lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Do not say, \u201CI will do to him as he has done to me;I will pay
        the man back for what he has done.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  I passed by the field of a sluggard,by the vineyard of a man lacking
        sense,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and behold, it was all overgrown with thorns;the ground was covered
        with nettles,and its stone wall was broken down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then I saw and considered it;I looked and received instruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: '  A little sleep, a little slumber,a little folding of the hands
        to rest,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: and poverty will come upon you like a robber,and want like an armed
        man.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: More Proverbs of Solomon'
      title: More Proverbs of Solomon
      number: 1
      content: '  These also are proverbs of Solomon which the men of Hezekiah king
        of Judah copied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It is the glory of God to conceal things,but the glory of kings is
        to search things out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'As the heavens for height, and the earth for depth,so the heart of
        kings is unsearchable.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Take away the dross from the silver,and the smith has material for
        a vessel;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'take away the wicked from the presence of the king,and his throne
        will be established in righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Do not put yourself forward in the king\u2019s presenceor stand in
        the place of the great,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "for it is better to be told, \u201CCome up here,\u201Dthan to be
        put lower in the presence of a noble.What your eyes have seen  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  do not hastily bring into court,[[COMMENT(0)]]for what will you
        do in the end,when your neighbor puts you to shame?  '
      comments:
      - number: '25:8 '
        content: 'Or Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  Argue your case with your neighbor himself,and do not reveal another\u2019s
        secret,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'lest he who hears you bring shame upon you,and your ill repute have
        no end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  A word fitly spokenis like apples of gold in a setting of silver.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Like a gold ring or an ornament of goldis a wise reprover to a listening
        ear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Like the cold of snow in the time of harvestis a faithful messenger
        to those who send him;he refreshes the soul of his masters.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Like clouds and wind without rainis a man who boasts of a gift he
        does not give.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'With patience a ruler may be persuaded,and a soft tongue will break
        a bone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'If you have found honey, eat only enough for you,lest you have your
        fill of it and vomit it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Let your foot be seldom in your neighbor\u2019s house,lest he have
        his fill of you and hate you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'A man who bears false witness against his neighboris like a war club,
        or a sword, or a sharp arrow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Trusting in a treacherous man in time of troubleis like a bad tooth
        or a foot that slips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Whoever sings songs to a heavy heartis like one who takes off a garment
        on a cold day,and like vinegar on soda.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  If your enemy is hungry, give him bread to eat,and if he is thirsty,
        give him water to drink,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'for you will heap burning coals on his head,and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will reward you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'The north wind brings forth rain,and a backbiting tongue, angry looks.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  It is better to live in a corner of the housetopthan in a house
        shared with a quarrelsome wife.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Like cold water to a thirsty soul,so is good news from a far country.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Like a muddied spring or a polluted fountainis a righteous man who
        gives way before the wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "It is not good to eat much honey,nor is it glorious to seek one\u2019s
        own glory.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '25:27 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew line is uncertain
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: A man without self-controlis like a city broken into and left without
        walls.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Like snow in summer or rain in harvest,so honor is not fitting
        for a fool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Like a sparrow in its flitting, like a swallow in its flying,  a
        curse that is causeless does not alight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  A whip for the horse, a bridle for the donkey,and a rod for the
        back of fools.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  Answer not a fool according to his folly,lest you be like him yourself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Answer a fool according to his folly,lest he be wise in his own
        eyes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Whoever sends a message by the hand of a foolcuts off his own feet
        and drinks violence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Like a lame man\u2019s legs, which hang useless,is a proverb in the
        mouth of fools.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Like one who binds the stone in the slingis one who gives honor to
        a fool.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Like a thorn that goes up into the hand of a drunkardis a proverb
        in the mouth of fools.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Like an archer who wounds everyoneis one who hires a passing fool
        or drunkard.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:10 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Like a dog that returns to his vomitis a fool who repeats his folly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Do you see a man who is wise in his own eyes?  There is more hope
        for a fool than for him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  The sluggard says, \u201CThere is a lion in the road!There is a
        lion in the streets!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'As a door turns on its hinges,so does a sluggard on his bed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  The sluggard buries his hand in the dish;it wears him out to bring
        it back to his mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The sluggard is wiser in his own eyes  than seven men who can answer
        sensibly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Whoever meddles in a quarrel not his ownis like one who takes a passing
        dog by the ears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Like a madman who throws firebrands, arrows, and death  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "is the man who deceives his neighborand says, \u201CI am only joking!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For lack of wood the fire goes out,and where there is no whisperer,
        quarreling ceases.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'As charcoal to hot embers and wood to fire,so is a quarrelsome man
        for kindling strife.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  The words of a whisperer are like delicious morsels;they go down
        into the inner parts of the body.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Like the glaze[[COMMENT(0)]] covering an earthen vesselare fervent
        lips with an evil heart.  '
      comments:
      - number: '26:23 '
        content: 'By revocalization; Hebrew '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Whoever hates disguises himself with his lipsand harbors deceit in
        his heart;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  when he speaks graciously, believe him not,for there are seven
        abominations in his heart;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'though his hatred be covered with deception,his wickedness will be
        exposed in the assembly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  Whoever digs a pit will fall into it,and a stone will come back
        on him who starts it rolling.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: A lying tongue hates its victims,and a flattering mouth works ruin.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Do not boast about tomorrow,  for you do not know what a day may
        bring.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Let another praise you, and not your own mouth;a stranger, and not
        your own lips.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "A stone is heavy, and sand is weighty,but a fool\u2019s provocation
        is heavier than both.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Wrath is cruel, anger is overwhelming,but who can stand before jealousy?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Better is open rebukethan hidden love.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Faithful are the wounds of a friend;profuse are the kisses of an
        enemy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'One who is full loathes honey,but to one who is hungry everything
        bitter is sweet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Like a bird that strays from its nestis a man who strays from his
        home.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Oil and perfume make the heart glad,and the sweetness of a friend
        comes from his earnest counsel.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Do not forsake your friend and your father\u2019s friend,and do not
        go to your brother\u2019s house in the day of your calamity.  Better is a
        neighbor who is nearthan a brother who is far away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Be wise, my son, and make my heart glad,that I may answer him who
        reproaches me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  The prudent sees danger and hides himself,but the simple go on
        and suffer for it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  Take a man\u2019s garment when he has put up security for a stranger,and
        hold it in pledge when he puts up security for an adulteress.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:13 '
        content: 'Hebrew ; a slight emendation yields (compare Vulgate; see also
          20:16) '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Whoever blesses his neighbor with a loud voice,rising early in the
        morning,will be counted as cursing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  A continual dripping on a rainy dayand a quarrelsome wife are alike;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "to restrain her is to restrain the windor to grasp[[COMMENT(0)]]
        oil in one\u2019s right hand.  "
      comments:
      - number: '27:16 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Iron sharpens iron,and one man sharpens another.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '27:17 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Whoever tends a fig tree will eat its fruit,and he who guards his
        master will be honored.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'As in water face reflects face,so the heart of man reflects the man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  Sheol and Abaddon are never satisfied,and never satisfied are the
        eyes of man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  The crucible is for silver, and the furnace is for gold,and a man
        is tested by his praise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  Crush a fool in a mortar with a pestlealong with crushed grain,yet
        his folly will not depart from him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Know well the condition of your flocks,and give attention to your
        herds,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'for riches do not last forever;and does a crown endure to all generations?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  When the grass is gone and the new growth appearsand the vegetation
        of the mountains is gathered,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  the lambs will provide your clothing,and the goats the price of
        a field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  There will be enough goats\u2019 milk for your food,for the food
        of your householdand maintenance for your girls."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    The wicked flee when no one pursues,but the righteous are bold
        as a lion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When a land transgresses, it has many rulers,but with a man of understanding
        and knowledge,its stability will long continue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  A poor man who oppresses the pooris a beating rain that leaves
        no food.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Those who forsake the law praise the wicked,but those who keep the
        law strive against them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Evil men do not understand justice,but those who seek the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        understand it completely.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Better is a poor man who walks in his integritythan a rich man
        who is crooked in his ways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The one who keeps the law is a son with understanding,but a companion
        of gluttons shames his father.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Whoever multiplies his wealth by interest and profit[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        gathers it for him who is generous to the poor.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:8 '
        content: That is, profit that comes from charging interest to the poor
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'If one turns away his ear from hearing the law,even his prayer is
        an abomination.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Whoever misleads the upright into an evil way  will fall into his
        own pit,but the blameless will have a goodly inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'A rich man is wise in his own eyes,but a poor man who has understanding
        will find him out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When the righteous triumph, there is great glory,but when the wicked
        rise, people hide themselves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Whoever conceals his transgressions will not prosper,but he who confesses
        and forsakes them will obtain mercy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Blessed is the one who fears the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>[[COMMENT(0)]]
        always,but whoever hardens his heart will fall into calamity.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Like a roaring lion or a charging bearis a wicked ruler over a poor
        people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'A ruler who lacks understanding is a cruel oppressor,but he who hates
        unjust gain will prolong his days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'If one is burdened with the blood of another,he will be a fugitive
        until death;[[COMMENT(0)]]let no one help him.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:17 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Whoever walks in integrity will be delivered,but he who is crooked
        in his ways will suddenly fall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  Whoever works his land will have plenty of bread,but he who follows
        worthless pursuits will have plenty of poverty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'A faithful man will abound with blessings,but whoever hastens to
        be rich will not go unpunished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'To show partiality is not good,but for a piece of bread a man will
        do wrong.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'A stingy man[[COMMENT(0)]]  hastens after wealthand does not know
        that poverty will come upon him.  '
      comments:
      - number: '28:22 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Whoever rebukes a man will afterward find more favorthan he who flatters
        with his tongue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Whoever robs his father or his motherand says, \u201CThat is no transgression,\u201Dis
        a companion to a man who destroys.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'A greedy man stirs up strife,but the one who trusts in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will be enriched.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Whoever trusts in his own mind is a fool,but he who walks in wisdom
        will be delivered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Whoever gives to the poor will not want,but he who hides his eyes
        will get many a curse.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: When the wicked rise, people hide themselves,but when they perish,
        the righteous increase.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '    He who is often reproved, yet stiffens his neck,will suddenly
        be broken beyond healing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When the righteous increase, the people rejoice,but when the wicked
        rule, the people groan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He who loves wisdom makes his father glad,but a companion of prostitutes
        squanders his wealth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'By justice a king builds up the land,but he who exacts gifts[[COMMENT(0)]]
        tears it down.  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  A man who flatters his neighborspreads a net for his feet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'An evil man is ensnared in his transgression,but a righteous man
        sings and rejoices.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'A righteous man knows the rights of the poor;a wicked man does not
        understand such knowledge.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Scoffers set a city aflame,but the wise turn away wrath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'If a wise man has an argument with a fool,the fool only rages and
        laughs, and there is no quiet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Bloodthirsty men hate one who is blamelessand seek the life of the
        upright.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:10 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'A fool gives full vent to his spirit,but a wise man quietly holds
        it back.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'If a ruler listens to falsehood,all his officials will be wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The poor man and the oppressor meet together;the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        gives light to the eyes of both.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If a king faithfully judges the poor,his throne will be established
        forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  The rod and reproof give wisdom,but a child left to himself brings
        shame to his mother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'When the wicked increase, transgression increases,but the righteous
        will look upon their downfall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Discipline your son, and he will give you rest;he will give delight
        to your heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Where there is no prophetic vision the people cast off restraint,[[COMMENT(0)]]but
        blessed is he who keeps the law.  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:18 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'By mere words a servant is not disciplined,for though he understands,
        he will not respond.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Do you see a man who is hasty in his words?  There is more hope for
        a fool than for him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Whoever pampers his servant from childhoodwill in the end find him
        his heir.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '29:21 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew word rendered is uncertain
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  A man of wrath stirs up strife,and one given to anger causes much
        transgression.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "  One\u2019s pride will bring him low,  but he who is lowly in spirit
        will obtain honor.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The partner of a thief hates his own life;  he hears the curse, but
        discloses nothing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  The fear of man lays a snare,but whoever trusts in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is safe.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Many seek the face of a ruler,but it is from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        that a man gets justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  An unjust man is an abomination to the righteous,but one whose
        way is straight is an abomination to the wicked.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Words of Agur'
      title: The Words of Agur
      number: 1
      content: '  The words of Agur son of Jakeh. The oracle.[[COMMENT(0)]]The man
        declares, I am weary, O God;I am weary, O God, and worn out.  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:1 '
        content: 'Or Revocalization; Hebrew '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Surely I am too stupid to be a man.I have not the understanding of
        a man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I have not learned wisdom,nor have I knowledge of the Holy One.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Who has ascended to heaven and come down?Who has gathered the wind
        in his fists?Who has wrapped up the waters in a garment?Who has established
        all the ends of the earth?  What is his name, and what is his son\u2019s
        name?Surely you know!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: '  Every word of God proves true;he is a shield to those who take
        refuge in him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Do not add to his words,lest he rebuke you and you be found a liar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Two things I ask of you;deny them not to me before I die:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Remove far from me falsehood and lying;give me neither poverty nor
        riches;feed me with the food that is needful for me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "lest I be full and deny youand say, \u201CWho is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u201Dor
        lest I be poor and steal  and profane the name of my God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Do not slander a servant to his master,  lest he curse you, and
        you be held guilty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'There are those[[COMMENT(0)]] who curse their fathersand do not bless
        their mothers.  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:11 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verses 12, 13, 14
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'There are those who are clean in their own eyesbut are not washed
        of their filth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "There are those\u2014how lofty are their eyes,how high their eyelids
        lift!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'There are those whose teeth are swords,whose fangs are knives,to
        devour the poor from off the earth,the needy from among mankind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "The leech has two daughters:Give and Give.[[COMMENT(0)]]  Three things
        are never satisfied;  four never say, \u201CEnough\u201D:  "
      comments:
      - number: '30:15 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "  Sheol, the barren womb,the land never satisfied with water,and
        the fire that never says, \u201CEnough.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The eye that mocks a fatherand scorns to obey a motherwill be picked
        out by the ravens of the valleyand eaten by the vultures.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Three things are too wonderful for me;  four I do not understand:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the way of an eagle in the sky,the way of a serpent on a rock,the
        way of a ship on the high seas,and the way of a man with a virgin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "This is the way of an adulteress:she eats and wipes her mouthand
        says, \u201CI have done no wrong.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Under three things the earth trembles;under four it cannot bear up:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  a slave when he becomes king,and a fool when he is filled with
        food;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  an unloved woman when she gets a husband,and a maidservant when
        she displaces her mistress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: '  Four things on earth are small,but they are exceedingly wise:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  the ants are a people not strong,yet they provide their food in
        the summer;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  the rock badgers are a people not mighty,yet they make their homes
        in the cliffs;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'the locusts have no king,yet all of them march in rank;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "the lizard you can take in your hands,yet it is in kings\u2019 palaces.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  Three things are stately in their tread;  four are stately in their
        stride:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'the lion, which is mightiest among beastsand does not turn back before
        any;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'the strutting rooster,[[COMMENT(0)]] the he-goat,and a king whose
        army is with him.  '
      comments:
      - number: '30:31 '
        content: 'Or , or ; Hebrew Or '
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'If you have been foolish, exalting yourself,or if you have been devising
        evil,  put your hand on your mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: For pressing milk produces curds,pressing the nose produces blood,and
        pressing anger produces strife.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Words of King Lemuel'
      title: The Words of King Lemuel
      number: 1
      content: '  The words of King Lemuel. An oracle that his mother taught him:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'What are you doing, my son?[[COMMENT(0)]] What are you doing, son
        of my womb?What are you doing, son of my vows?  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:2 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Do not give your strength to women,your ways to those who destroy
        kings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  It is not for kings, O Lemuel,it is not for kings to drink wine,or
        for rulers to take strong drink,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'lest they drink and forget what has been decreedand pervert the rights
        of all the afflicted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Give strong drink to the one who is perishing,and wine to those in
        bitter distress;[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:6 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  let them drink and forget their povertyand remember their misery
        no more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  Open your mouth for the mute,for the rights of all who are destitute.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew   '
    - name: '9: The Woman Who Fears the '
      title: 'The Woman Who Fears the '
      number: 9
      content: 'Open your mouth, judge righteously,  defend the rights of the poor
        and needy.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  [[COMMENT(0)]]  An excellent wife who can find?She is far more
        precious than jewels.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:10 '
        content: "  Verses 10\u201331 are an acrostic poem, each verse beginning
          with the successive letters of the Hebrew alphabet  "
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The heart of her husband trusts in her,and he will have no lack of
        gain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'She does him good, and not harm,all the days of her life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'She seeks wool and flax,and works with willing hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'She is like the ships of the merchant;she brings her food from afar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'She rises while it is yet nightand provides food for her householdand
        portions for her maidens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'She considers a field and buys it;with the fruit of her hands she
        plants a vineyard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'She dresses herself[[COMMENT(0)]] with strengthand makes her arms
        strong.  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:17 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'She perceives that her merchandise is profitable.Her lamp does not
        go out at night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'She puts her hands to the distaff,and her hands hold the spindle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'She opens her hand to the poorand reaches out her hands to the needy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'She is not afraid of snow for her household,for all her household
        are clothed in scarlet.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '31:21 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'She makes bed coverings for herself;her clothing is fine linen and
        purple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Her husband is known in the gateswhen he sits among the elders of
        the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'She makes linen garments and sells them;she delivers sashes to the
        merchant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  Strength and dignity are her clothing,and she laughs at the time
        to come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'She opens her mouth with wisdom,and the teaching of kindness is on
        her tongue.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'She looks well to the ways of her householdand does not eat the bread
        of idleness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Her children rise up and call her blessed;her husband also, and he
        praises her:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CMany women have done excellently,but you surpass them all.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: '  Charm is deceitful, and beauty is vain,but a woman who fears the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is to be praised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Give her of the fruit of her hands,and let her works praise her in
        the gates.
      comments: []
